    "department": "Deliveroo Cost Center Hierarchy",
    "description": "About the role\n\nWe’re looking for a highly motivated marketer to join the Deliveroo Italy marketing team, who will report to the Senior Brand \u0026 Media Manager, to support the planning, execution, and optimization of Deliveroo’s brand and media activities.\n\nThe ideal candidate will work closely with local and global teams, media and creative agencies, and cross-functional stakeholders to drive brand awareness, consideration, and overall campaign effectiveness through integrated, multi-channel campaigns.\n\nWe’re looking for an entrepreneurial, hands-on brand builder with a strong understanding of media who enjoys working across channels, shaping campaigns, and making things happen. You have a passion for brand building and a strategic mindset to translate business challenges into impactful communication and media plans. You’re a self-starter who is comfortable with ambiguity in fast-moving, ever-changing environments.\n\nWhat you'll be doing\n\n - Brand \u0026 Media Strategy Execution: Support the definition of local brand and media strategy, translating global guidelines into effective local plans, ensuring consistency and business impact.\n\n - Media Planning \u0026 Budget Management: Lead the planning, allocation, and optimization of ATL media budgets, working closely with local media agencies and global teams.\n\n - Integrated Campaigns Execution and Coordination: Drive the execution of multi-channel campaigns, working closely with local and global stakeholders and cross-functional teams to ensure full-funnel alignment and maximize campaign impact.\n\n - Creative Production \u0026 Localization: Collaborate with global brand teams to coordinate the creative development and localization process of global brand campaigns, ensuring all assets are aligned with local needs and objectives.\n\n - Measurement \u0026 Effectiveness: Contribute to defining KPIs and measurement frameworks, working closely with BI and Data Science teams to analyze performance, derive actionable insights, and optimize future activities.\n\n - Agency Management: Manage day-to-day relationships with media and creative agencies, ensuring high-quality execution and alignment with strategic objectives.\n\nRequirements\n\n - 4–6 years of experience in brand and media roles (agency or in-house).\n\n - Good knowledge of the Italian media landscape, including key ATL channels (TV, VOD/BVOD, OOH, Radio) and main agencies and vendors.\n\n - Experience in planning and executing multi-channel campaigns, with increasing level of ownership.\n\n - Solid understanding of campaign measurement and performance analysis; familiarity with brand and ATL measurement methodologies (e.g. TV effectiveness, brand lift, econometrics/MMM) is a strong plus.\n\n - Highly skilled in the English language, both written and spoken, with the ability to work in an international environment.\n\n - Strong strategic and executional mindset, with the ability to manage complexity, prioritize effectively, and deliver against multiple projects in a fast-paced environment.\n\n - Highly proactive and solution-oriented, with a self-starter attitude, strong sense of ownership, and ability to navigate ambiguity and change.\n\n - Excellent stakeholder management and communication skills, with the ability to influence cross-functional teams and manage agency relationships effectively.\n   \n   Why Deliveroo\n\nOur mission is to transform the way you shop and eat, bringing the neighbourhood to your door by connecting consumers, restaurants, shops and riders. We are transforming the way the world eats and shops by making access to food and products more convenient and enjoyable. We give people the opportunity to buy what they want, as they want it, when and where they want it.\n\nWe are a technology-driven company at the forefront of the most rapidly expanding industry in the world. We are still a small team, making a very large impact, looking to answer some of the most interesting questions out there. We move fast, value autonomy and ownership, and we are always looking for new ideas.\n\nWorkplace \u0026 Benefits\n\nAt Deliveroo we know that people are the heart of the business and we prioritise their welfare. Benefits differ by country, but we offer many benefits in areas including healthcare, well-being, parental leave, pensions, and generous annual leave allowances, including time off to support a charitable cause of your choice. Benefits are country-specific, please ask your recruiter for more information.\n\nDiversity\n\nAt Deliveroo, we believe a great workplace is one that represents the world we live in and how beautifully diverse it can be. That means we have no judgement when it comes to any one of the things that make you who you are - your gender, race, sexuality, religion or a secret aversion to coriander. All you need is a passion for (most) food and a desire to be part of one of the fastest-growing businesses in a rapidly growing industry.\n\nWe are committed to diversity, equity and inclusion in all aspects of our hiring process. We recognise that some candidates may require adjustments to apply for a position or fairly participate in the interview process. If you require any adjustments, please don't hesitate to let us know. We will make every effort to provide the necessary adjustments to ensure you have an equitable opportunity to succeed.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
    "is_active": true,
